OL,3,CBritain facing a water scarcity
OL,4,Ccrisis. What is being done to prevent
OL,5,Cit?
OL,7,FEngland alone faces a shortfall of
OL,8,Ffive billion litres of water a day -
OL,9,Fthat's over two million wheelie bins
OL,10,Ffull of water every day - by 2050,
OL,11,Faccording to figures from the
OL,12,FEnvironment Agency.
OL,14,FMany parts of England are already
OL,15,Fexperiencing water shortages. England
OL,16,Fas a whole has had its driest spring
OL,17,Fsince 1929. Reservoirs are running
OL,18,Flow. In the North West of England, a
OL,19,Fdrought has been declared.
