OL,3,CBritain facing a water scarcity
OL,4,Ccrisis. What is being done to prevent
OL,5,Cit?
OL,7,FEngland and Wales' reservoirs have
OL,8,Fcapacity to hold 1,600 gigalitres of
OL,9,Fwater. To put that in context,
OL,10,FAustralia, a much drier country, has
OL,11,F84,000 gigalitres of storage capacity.
OL,13,FNo new reservoirs have been built here
OL,14,Fin 30 years. The government has
OL,15,Fannounced plans to build nine, but
OL,16,Fthese will not all be online until the
OL,17,F2040s.
